  "texts": [
    "However, JSL is not able to distinguish between notes related to general housing and housing instability, and Regex has low precision and recall for identifying notes related to housing instability.",
    "Therefore, the LLMs provide the best chance of finding relevant notes related to housing/housing instability for patients in either class.",
    "Because the number of notes flagged by GPT-4 and GPT-3.5 were very low in the preliminary negative class (12 and 11, respectively, out of 5,455 notes), the two models would need to analyze approximately 227,300 notes to find ~500 notes related to housing and/or housing instability in the preliminary negative class.",
    "Due to the cost restrictions of running these LLMs, we were unable to perform this analysis.",
    "However, future work to analyze additional notes from patients in the preliminary negative class could provide insight into any differences in notes between these two classes."
